{
  "texts": [
    "Despite the introduction of various GNNs such as CGCNN, MEGNet, ALIGNN, and coGN since 2018, which have made substantial achievements in aspects like global state variable representation, incorporation of bond angle information, and optimization of crystal graph edge connections, there are still some problems that need to be overcome.",
    "First, we observe that nested graph networks like ALIGNN and coGN, while effective in certain cases, are limited in their widespread application due to high training costs and advantages on only specific datasets.",
    "To tackle these problems, we introduce LOPE to optimize the atomic embedding representation and edge connectivity, effectively learn multi-body interactions such as bond angles and local geometric distortions, and achieve minimal edge connections.",
    "This reduces the training time required for larger GNNs without sacrificing accuracy.",
    "Second, we introduce the DenseGNN model to address the problems of extending GNN to diverse applications in materials, molecular, and chemical fields."
  ]
}